                                                    BRIEF-Limelight Networks Q2 loss per share $0.01
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    4:13 PM ET 07/26/2017
                                                


Limelight Networks Inc (LLNW). * Limelight Networks (LLNW) reports financial results for the second quarter of 2017. * Q2 non-GAAP earnings per share $0.03. * Q2 GAAP loss per share $0.01. * Q2 revenue $45.4 million versus I/B/E/S view $45.2 million.

















                                                    Limelight Networks Reports Financial Results for the Second Quarter of 2017
                                                


                                                    Business Wire – 
                                                    4:01 PM ET 07/26/2017
                                                


TEMPE, Ariz. Gross margin was 47.1% in the second quarter of 2017, an increase of 390 basis points from 43.2% in the second quarter of 2016. On a GAAP basis, Limelight reported a net loss of $1.6 million, or $0.01 per basic share, for the second quarter of 2017, compared to a net loss of $57.9 million, or $0.56 per basic share, in the second quarter of 2016.

















                                                    Limelight Networks Expands Its Content Delivery Network Capacity in India with Three New Points-of-Presence
                                                


                                                    Business Wire – 
                                                    10:00 PM ET 07/19/2017
                                                


Move Addresses Market Demand for World Class CDN Services and Capabilities Limelight Networks, Inc. (LLNW), a global leader in digital content delivery, today announced the opening of three new Points-of-Presence in India. Movies, music and sports are the foundation of digital content for the 1.3 billion people of India.

















                                                    Primerica Uses Limelight Networks to Live Stream Company Meetings and Store Videos for On-Demand Viewing on Multiple Devices
                                                


                                                    Business Wire – 
                                                    10:03 AM ET 06/28/2017
                                                


Limelight Networks (LLNW), a global leader in digital content delivery, announced today that Primerica is using its Content Delivery Network for company-wide live broadcasts and for on-demand viewing of hundreds of training and recognition videos. Before Limelight, we couldnt deliver live video to all of our employees simultaneously, said Mike Ziegenbein, VP and Chief Engineer at Primerica.

















                                                    Limelight Networks, Inc. to Issue Second Quarter 2017 Financial Results on Wednesday, July 26, 2017, after the Market Close
                                                


                                                    Business Wire – 
                                                    10:56 AM ET 06/20/2017
                                                


Limelight Networks, Inc. (LLNW) will report financial results for the second quarter 2017 on Wednesday, July 26, 2017 at 4:00 p.m. EDT. Management will host a quarterly conference call for investors at 4:30 p.m. EDT. The conference call will also be audio cast live from http://investors.limelight.com/ and a replay will be available following the call from the Company's website. About Limelight.

















                                                    Consumer Preferences Shift to Digital Content Reveals Limelight Networks’ New ‘State of Digital Downloads’ Report
                                                


                                                    Business Wire – 
                                                    9:53 AM ET 06/13/2017
                                                


Video games, books, music and magazines are now purchased online more often than physical copies. Consumers worldwide increasingly depend on smartphones to access digital content and tend to go online to purchase video games, movies and books, according to the latest State of Digital Downloads research report from Limelight Networks (LLNW), a global leader in digital content delivery.

















